<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="163" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,259,681]" pageId="12" pageNumber="163">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,475,501]" pageId="12" pageNumber="163">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species is widespread throughout West Africa (Antoine 2005; 
<bibRefCitation author="Beinhundner, G." box="[1071,1298,475,502]" pageId="12" pageNumber="163" refId="ref23523" refString="Beinhundner, G. (2017 b) The Cetoniinae of Africa (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). Privately published, Euerbach, Germany, 1199 pp." type="book" year="2017">Beinhundner 2017b</bibRefCitation>
). Ecological data and a basic guideline to captive breeding are available for a closely related species [
<taxonomicName authority="(DeGeer, 1778)" baseAuthorityName="DeGeer" baseAuthorityYear="1778" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Phonotaenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="163" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteata">
<emphasis box="[1200,1323,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="163">P. balteata</emphasis>
(DeGeer, 1778)
</taxonomicName>
] (
<bibRefCitation author="Marais, E. &amp; Holm, E." box="[240,484,547,573]" pageId="12" pageNumber="163" pagination="1 - 125" refId="ref27798" refString="Marais, E. &amp; Holm, E. (1992) Type catalogue and bibliography of the Cetoniinae of Sub-Saharan Africa. Cimbebasia Memoir, 8, 1 - 125." type="journal article" year="1992">Holm &amp; Marais 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Malec, P. &amp; Sipek, P." box="[495,731,547,576]" pageId="12" pageNumber="163" pagination="52 - 78" refId="ref27681" refString="Malec, P. &amp; Sipek, P. (2016) On the cetoniine fauna of Eastern Cape (EC) and KwaZulu-Natal (KZN) and the basic guidelines to captive breeding of these beetles (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae, Cetoniinae). Cetoniimania, Nouvelle Serie, 9, 52 - 78." type="journal article" year="2016">Malec &amp; Šípek 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Biodiversity information (abundance, habitat preference) was provided for GHA by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mudge, A. D. &amp; Orozco, J. &amp; Philips, T. K. &amp; Antoine, Ph." box="[396,618,583,609]" pageId="12" pageNumber="163" pagination="113 - 174" refId="ref28568" refString="Mudge, A. D., Orozco, J., Philips, T. K. &amp; Antoine, Ph. (2012) The cetoniine fauna of the Upper Guinean forests and savannas of Ghana (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Cetoniinae). Terrestrial Arthropod Reviews, 5, 113 - 174. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187498312 X 635319" type="journal article" year="2012">
Mudge 
<emphasis box="[482,537,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="163">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Joly, C." box="[671,799,583,609]" pageId="12" pageNumber="163" pagination="28 - 89" refId="ref26401" refString="Joly, C. (2018) Deuxieme contribution a la connaissance des Cetoniidae du Ghana, sous-familles des Cetoniinae et des Trichinae (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae). Lambillionea, 118 (1), 28 - 89." type="journal article" year="2018">Joly (2018)</bibRefCitation>
and for BEN by 
<bibRefCitation author="Touroult, J. &amp; Le Gall, Ph." box="[988,1286,583,610]" pageId="12" pageNumber="163" pagination="23 - 34" refId="ref31782" refString="Touroult, J. &amp; Le Gall, Ph. (2013) Fruit feeding Cetoniinae community structure in an anthropogenic landscape in West Africa. Journal of Insect Conservation, 17, 23 - 34. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10841 - 012 - 9483 - 2" type="journal article" year="2013">Touroult &amp; Le Gall (2013)</bibRefCitation>
. The Guinea- 
<collectingRegion box="[151,226,619,645]" country="Guinea-Bissau" name="Bissau" pageId="12" pageNumber="163">Bissau</collectingRegion>
adult specimens were sampled by CT (
<figureCitation box="[658,741,619,646]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,183,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[202,1385,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. a, butterfly trap baited with banana and pineapple, Béli - Petaqui, GAB; b, yellow chromotropic trap baited with banana, Coli (Quebo), TOB; c, light trapping, Balana river (Mampatá), TOB; d, herbaceous and shrubby savanna, Béli, GAB; e, open forest, Coli (Quebo), TOB; f, primary moist forest, Canamina (Jemberem), TOB; g, clearance by fire to shift agricultural plantation, Coli (Quebo), TOB; h, artisanal charcoal sale, Buba—Tunani, QUN." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6280704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6280704/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="163">Fig. 2b</figureCitation>
). It is a new species record for the CAC Administrative Region of 
<collectingCountry box="[182,351,655,681]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="12" pageNumber="163">Guinea-Bissau</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
